From: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Date: Mon, 22 Jul 2019 20:47:08 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] x86/apic: Soft disable APIC before initializing it
References: bnc#1151927
Patch-mainline: 5.3.4
Git-commit: 2640da4cccf5cc613bf26f0998b9e340f4b5f69c

[ Upstream commit 2640da4cccf5cc613bf26f0998b9e340f4b5f69c ]

If the APIC was already enabled on entry of setup_local_APIC() then
disabling it soft via the SPIV register makes a lot of sense.

That masks all LVT entries and brings it into a well defined state.

Otherwise previously enabled LVTs which are not touched in the setup
function stay unmasked and might surprise the just booting kernel.

Signed-off-by: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Acked-by: Peter Zijlstra (Intel) <peterz@infradead.org>
Link: https://lkml.kernel.org/r/20190722105219.068290579@linutronix.de
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 arch/x86/kernel/apic/apic.c | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/x86/kernel/apic/apic.c b/arch/x86/kernel/apic/apic.c
index 436d462dde71..ad0d5ced82b3 100644
--- a/arch/x86/kernel/apic/apic.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kernel/apic/apic.c
@@ -1583,6 +1583,14 @@ static void setup_local_APIC(void)
 		return;
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * If this comes from kexec/kcrash the APIC might be enabled in
+	 * SPIV. Soft disable it before doing further initialization.
+	 */
+	value = apic_read(APIC_SPIV);
+	value &= ~APIC_SPIV_APIC_ENABLED;
+	apic_write(APIC_SPIV, value);
+
 #ifdef CONFIG_X86_32
 	/* Pound the ESR really hard over the head with a big hammer - mbligh */
 	if (lapic_is_integrated() && apic->disable_esr) {
